<subSubSection id="69ABB7FA9B17FFB492AEFB7E4AEE1BC0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="210EE4719B17FFB492AEFB7E4D9D182C" blockId="16.[151,1437,1142,1778]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB492AEFB7E4E491981" bold="true" box="[199,315,1179,1203]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The following species of 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB49002FB7E4DC61980" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[619,692,1179,1202]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB49002FB7E4DC61980" box="[619,692,1179,1202]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pepsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were represented in our studied sample: 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB496F8FB7E4E7019E4" authority="Palisot de Beauvois" authorityName="Palisot de Beauvois" authorityYear="1809" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB496F8FB7E4A501980" box="[1169,1314,1179,1202]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. marginata</emphasis>
Palisot de Beauvois
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB49378FB5A4EA619E4" authority="(Drury)" baseAuthorityName="Drury" baseAuthorityYear="1773" box="[273,468,1214,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubra">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB49378FB5A4E0319E4" box="[273,369,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. rubra</emphasis>
(Drury)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4907EFB5A4C5D19E4" authority="(Fabricius)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" box="[535,815,1214,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficornis">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB4907EFB5A4DD719E4" box="[535,677,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. ruficornis</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB49157FB5B4B4F19E4" author="Perez-Gelabert, D. E." box="[830,1085,1214,1238]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 530" refId="ref45075" refString="Perez-Gelabert, D. E. (2008) Arthropods of Hispaniola (Dominican Republic and Haiti), a checklist and bibliography. Zootaxa, 1831, 1 - 530." type="journal article" year="2008">Perez-Gelabert (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, however, recorded additional species for the Hisponiola Island: 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB49072FB064C4B19C8" authority="Mocsary" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1888" box="[539,825,1250,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cassiope">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB49072FB064DBE19C8" box="[539,716,1251,1274]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pepsis cassiope</emphasis>
Mocsáry
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4912CFB064B3A19C8" authority="(Linnaeus)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[837,1096,1250,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Sphex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB4912CFB064CB619C9" box="[837,964,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. caerulea</emphasis>
(Linnaeus)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4963CFB064A6719C8" authority="Mocsary" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1885" box="[1109,1301,1250,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB4963CFB064BD819C8" box="[1109,1194,1251,1274]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. nana</emphasis>
Mocsáry
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4974BFB064E78182C" authority="Lepeletier" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericans">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB4974BFB064AEE19C8" box="[1314,1436,1251,1274]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. sericans</emphasis>
Lepeletier
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4932DFAE24D9D182C" authority="Palisot de Beauvois." box="[324,751,1286,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphuricornis">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB4932DFAE24D71182C" box="[324,515,1286,1310]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. sulphuricornis</emphasis>
Palisot de Beauvois.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="210EE4719B17FFB492AEFACF4CFD1BB4" blockId="16.[151,1437,1142,1778]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
There are several issues concerning the distribution and validity of the species recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB4969DFACF4F961854" author="Perez-Gelabert, D. E." pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 530" refId="ref45075" refString="Perez-Gelabert, D. E. (2008) Arthropods of Hispaniola (Dominican Republic and Haiti), a checklist and bibliography. Zootaxa, 1831, 1 - 530." type="journal article" year="2008">Perez-Gelabert (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB49299FAAA4ED01854" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[240,418,1358,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB49299FAAA4ED01854" box="[240,418,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pepsis caerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB493B0FAAA4DEA1854" box="[473,664,1358,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphuricornis">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB493B0FAAA4DEA1854" box="[473,664,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. sulphuricornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are no longer recognized as 
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB491B5FAAA4B5E1854" box="[988,1068,1359,1382]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB491B5FAAA4B5A1854" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[988,1064,1359,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pepsis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
These species were classified as 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB492FEFA964F8318B8" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1843" box="[151,241,1395,1418]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Entypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB492FEFA964F8318B8" box="[151,241,1395,1418]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Entypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB4934FFA964EDE18B8" author="Day, M. C." box="[294,428,1394,1419]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="45 - 84" refId="ref42946" refString="Day, M. C. (1979) The species of Hymenoptera described by Linnaeus in the genera Sphex, Chrysis, Vespa, Apis and Mutilla. Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 12, 45 - 84." type="journal article" year="1979">Day (1979)</bibRefCitation>
(see 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4939AFA964D3F18B8" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1843" box="[499,589,1395,1418]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Entypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB4939AFA964D3F18B8" box="[499,589,1395,1418]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Entypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
section). 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB490AFFA964C0E18B8" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1888" box="[710,892,1395,1418]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cassiope">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB490AFFA964C0E18B8" box="[710,892,1395,1418]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pepsis cassiope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found from the Southern 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB496B2FA974A6118B8" box="[1243,1299,1394,1418]" name="United States of America" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">USA</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB4972AFA974AEA18B8" box="[1347,1432,1394,1418]" name="Bolivia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB492FEFA734E77189C" box="[151,261,1430,1454]" name="Colombia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Colombia</collectingCountry>
east through 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB493CDFA734E89189C" box="[420,507,1430,1454]" name="Guyana" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Guyana</collectingCountry>
to the Amazon delta, and the southeast coast of 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB49659FA734B06189C" box="[1072,1140,1430,1454]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB496EDFA734A62189C" author="Vardy, C. R." box="[1156,1296,1430,1454]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 133" refId="ref45803" refString="Vardy, C. R. (2002) The New World tarantula-hawk wasp genus Pepsis Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae), Part 2. The P. grossa - to P. deurata - groups. Zoologische Verhandelinden, 338, 1 - 133." type="journal article" year="2002">Vardy 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The single records for 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB49375FA5F4E0318E0" box="[284,369,1466,1490]" name="Mexico" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB493C5FA5F4DE418E0" box="[428,662,1466,1490]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
are dubious (
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB4915AFA5F4CCC18E0" author="Vardy, C. R." box="[819,958,1466,1490]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 133" refId="ref45803" refString="Vardy, C. R. (2002) The New World tarantula-hawk wasp genus Pepsis Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae), Part 2. The P. grossa - to P. deurata - groups. Zoologische Verhandelinden, 338, 1 - 133." type="journal article" year="2002">Vardy 2002</bibRefCitation>
). As pointed by 
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB49615FA5F4A0818E0" author="Perez-Gelabert, D. E." box="[1148,1402,1466,1490]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 530" refId="ref45075" refString="Perez-Gelabert, D. E. (2008) Arthropods of Hispaniola (Dominican Republic and Haiti), a checklist and bibliography. Zootaxa, 1831, 1 - 530." type="journal article" year="2008">Perez-Gelabert (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB497EEFA5E4FBD18C4" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB497EEFA5E4FBD18C4" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found only in South America in the eastern Andes, and the specimens recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB496A5FA3B4A7618C4" box="[1228,1284,1502,1526]" name="Haiti" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Haiti</collectingCountry>
are probably mislabeled (
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB4934AF9E74EC21B28" author="Vardy, C. R." box="[291,432,1538,1562]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 305" refId="ref45850" refString="Vardy, C. R. (2005) The New World tarantula-hawk wasp genus Pepsis Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae), Part 3. The P. inclyta - to P. auriguttata- groups. Zoologische Mededelingen Leiden, 79 (5), 1 - 305." type="journal article" year="2005">Vardy 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB493A1F9E64D081B28" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1845" box="[456,634,1539,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericans">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB493A1F9E64D081B28" box="[456,634,1539,1562]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pepsis sericans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the senior synonym of a complex of names that includes 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4973AF9E64EEF1B0C" authority="Lepeletier" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domingensis">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB4973AF9E64E511B0C" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pepsis domingensis</emphasis>
Lepeletier
</taxonomicName>
and its variaties (
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB49007F9C34D881B0C" author="Vardy, C. R." box="[622,762,1574,1598]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 86" refId="ref45760" refString="Vardy, C. R. (2000) The New World tarantula-hawk wasp genus Pepsis Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae), Part 1. Introduction and the P. rubra species-group. Zoologische Verhandelinden, 332, 1 - 86." type="journal article" year="2000">Vardy 2000</bibRefCitation>
). Although 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB491EBF9C24B5E1B0C" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1845" box="[898,1068,1574,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domingensis">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB491EBF9C24B5E1B0C" box="[898,1068,1574,1598]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. domingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been described from 
<collectingRegion id="E3752A939B17FFB49735F9C34E761B50" country="Dominican Republic" name="Santo Domingo" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Santo Domingo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB49379F9AF4E8E1B50" box="[272,508,1610,1634]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="452099809B17FFB49061F9AF4DEC1B50" author="Vardy, C. R." box="[520,670,1610,1634]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="1 - 86" refId="ref45760" refString="Vardy, C. R. (2000) The New World tarantula-hawk wasp genus Pepsis Fabricius (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae), Part 1. Introduction and the P. rubra species-group. Zoologische Verhandelinden, 332, 1 - 86." type="journal article" year="2000">Vardy (2000)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4919DF9AE4B1C1B50" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1845" box="[1012,1134,1611,1634]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericans">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB4919DF9AE4B1C1B50" box="[1012,1134,1611,1634]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. sericans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is limited to 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB4976FF9AF4A331B50" box="[1286,1345,1610,1634]" name="Cuba" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Cuba</collectingCountry>
and the record of this species from 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB493A1F98B4D1C1BB4" box="[456,622,1646,1670]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic is also dubious.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="210EE4719B17FFB492AEF9764AEE1BC0" blockId="16.[151,1437,1142,1778]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Because our study did not reveal any of these species in 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB49129F9774C971B98" box="[832,997,1682,1706]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic, because 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB496D6F9764A7A1B98" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[1215,1288,1683,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB496D6F9764A7A1B98" box="[1215,1288,1683,1706]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pepsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently reviewed, and because these species have dubious records attributed to 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB491B8F9534B0B1BFC" box="[977,1145,1718,1742]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB49691F9524A041BFC" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1888" box="[1272,1398,1719,1742]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cassiope">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB49691F9524A041BFC" box="[1272,1398,1719,1742]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. cassiope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB497EEF9524FBD1BC0" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB497EEF9524FBD1BC0" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB49362F93E4EF11BC0" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1845" box="[267,387,1755,1778]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Pepsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericans">
<emphasis id="13C538639B17FFB49362F93E4EF11BC0" box="[267,387,1755,1778]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">P. sericans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were not included in our key nor in our list of species of 
<collectingCountry id="59A6A4E19B17FFB49197F93F4BD11BC0" box="[1022,1187,1754,1778]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic 
<taxonomicName id="E6B19FF29B17FFB4977CF93F4AEA1BC0" box="[1301,1432,1754,1778]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pompilidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
